{% extends 'bas_style_kit/layouts/bsk_standard.j2' %}

{% block main_content %}
<header class="bsk-page-header bsk-page-header-stacked">
  <h1>
    <small>Profile</small>
    <br>
    ISO 19115 - EU INSPIRE
  </h1>
</header>

<div class="bsk-row">
    <div class="bsk-col-12-md-10">
        <a href="https://inspire.ec.europa.eu/about-inspire/563">EU INSPIRE</a> is a profile implemented on top of the
        <a href="/standards/iso-19115">ISO 19115 (19139)</a> standard.

        <section>
            <h2>Guidance</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://inspire.ec.europa.eu/documents/inspire-metadata-implementing-rules-technical-guidelines-based-en-iso-19115-and-en-iso-1">Inspire Technical Guidance for ISO 19115 (profile)</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://inspire.ec.europa.eu/id/document/tg/metadata-iso19139">Inspire Technical Guidance for ISO 19139 (for datasets) (profile)</a></li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="validation">
            <h2>Validation</h2>
            <p class="bsk-alert bsk-alert-highlight bsk-alert-info">
                See the <a class="bsk-alert-link" href="/about#validation">about</a> page for general information on
                how metadata records are validated.
            </p>
            <p>Records can be validated against this profile using the
                <a href="http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/validator/about/">INSPIRE validator service</a>.</p>
            <p>The INSPIRE validator consists of multiple conformance classes, of which our records should be compliant with:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/id/ats/metadata/1.3/xml-encoding">XML encoding of ISO 19115/19119 metadata</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/id/ats/metadata/1.3/iso-19115-19119">INSPIRE Profile based on EN ISO 19115 and EN ISO 19119</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/id/ats/data/master/interoperability-metadata">Metadata for interoperability</a></li>
            </ul>
            <p class="bsk-alert bsk-alert-highlight bsk-alert-info">
                Note that the <em>Metadata for interoperability</em> conformance class requires a version for all data
                format elements. In cases where this isn't known INSPIRE does not support the conventional
                <code>gco:nilReason</code> attribute. Therefore it is acceptable to fail this conformance class.
            </p>
            <h3>Inspire validation compatibility</h3>
            <p>Use <em>INSPIRE compatible</em> versions of sample records when using the INSPIRE validator. This will change the
                schema location attribute (<code>xsi:schemaLocation</code>) to use an INSPIRE provided XSD for the
                <code>http://www.isotc211.org/2005/gmd</code> namespace. This is a
                <a href="https://github.com/inspire-eu-validation/community/issues/37">known limitation</a> of the validator.</p>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
